						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into the central shrine in the Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrarājēndradēva. Year 27: A.D. 1233.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Kāḷividiyāṉ Sundarapperumāḷ, a <hi rend="italic">kaikkōla</hi> resident of Adirādarāchaṉ <hi rend="italic">tirumaḍaiviḷāgam</hi>, erected two door-posts in the temple of Tirunāgīchchuram Uḍaiyār.</p>						

